You can run the preview for all visible documents or a subgroup of them from the **Preview **page using the view selector.

In the **Preview **area it is possible to generate a graphic preview of the document as it is presented in the print spool generation phase.

It is possible to start the preview of all documents or a few only.

The preview format can be PDF, AFP, raster, PCL or Postscript, depending on the Target configuration.

When generating the preview, Document Composition checks the entire document for any errors generated during the composition and editing phases. Any errors found will be summarized in a report that can be consulted when the preview has been completed. You can run an instant preview using the panel on the top bar.

> Tip

As you proceed with your editing, it is recommended to run frequent previews of the document.

> Warning

It is recommended to verify the correctness of the file used to generate the preview before proceeding.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

## Document selection panel
**![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)**

**Term**

**Description**

**Use approved versions if available**

Select whether to include only approved versions of the document, or not. When the option is enabled only approved documents will be used.

**Search box**

To perform a search, enter the text to be used as a search parameter (substring, case insensitive). The matching items (if any) will be listed in the panel below.

**Document type selection**

Select the document type:

- **All**: select all documents in the list.

- **None**: deselect all documents in the list.

- **Approved**: select all documents that have approved versions and deselects the rest.

- **Enabled**: enable all active documents and deselect the rest.

**Document selection**

Include the document in the preview operation.

## **Selecting one or more documents**
Use one of the procedures below to select the documents to be tested from the selection panel. 

-  Expand the desired family and select the checkbox next to the name of each document.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,) 

-  Use the predefined selection options (**All**, **None**, **Approved**, **Enabled**) to select multiple documents at once.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,) 

## Setting the preview options
**![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)**

### Activating a front and back preview
Select the **Duplex **checkbox to activate the front and back preview.

### Checking overflow
This option allows you to simulate the maximum occupation of variable data defined in the data contract. To use the overflow simulation feature in the document's content editor:

- Log in to the Doxee Platform.

- Access the **Design **scope of a production application.

- Launch the editor of a DC resource document.

- Select the **Preview **tab.

- Select the **Check overflow **option.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,) 

- Click **Start **to upload an input data file (below an example):

`&lt;?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" ?&gt;
&lt;FILE file-attribute="field1"&gt;
   &lt;DOCUMENT document-attribute="field1"&gt;
      &lt;TEMPLATE template-attribute="field1" account="accn=my-account,p=Doxee Platform"&gt;
         &lt;ELEMENTO1 elemento-attribute="accn=my-account,p=Doxee Platform"&gt;&lt;/ELEMENTO1&gt;
      &lt;/TEMPLATE&gt;
   &lt;/DOCUMENT&gt;
   &lt;DOCUMENT document-attribute="field2"&gt;
      &lt;TEMPLATE template-attribute="field2" account="accn=my-account,p=Doxee Platform"&gt;
         &lt;ELEMENTO1 elemento-attribute="accn=my-account,p=Doxee Platform"&gt;&lt;/ELEMENTO1&gt;
      &lt;/TEMPLATE&gt;
   &lt;/DOCUMENT&gt;
   &lt;DOCUMENT document-attribute="field1"&gt;
      &lt;TEMPLATE template-attribute="field1" account="accn=my-account,p=Doxee Platform"&gt;
         &lt;ELEMENTO1 elemento-attribute="accn=my-account,p=Doxee Platform"&gt;&lt;/ELEMENTO1&gt;
      &lt;/TEMPLATE&gt;
   &lt;/DOCUMENT&gt;
&lt;/FILE&gt;`> Note

The rule set selection is guided by the data file loaded for the preview, thus providing a simulation of a specific case.

If the preview fails due to text overflow, click **Download archive**; in the downloaded ZIP file you will find an *outputPath *folder containing the PDF file of the preview in which the text overflow occurred.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

Otherwise, click **Download spool **to get the PDF file of the preview.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

> Warning

All non-dynamic variable string data bindings in the template will be replaced with the characters of the data file loaded by the user for the maximum length of the contract attribute (data schema section). When the limit is reached, the text will be cut.

### Using the advanced settings
Administrators can access to further range preview options. This permits to apply personalized output settings directly. In this window you can configure some of the output management options, described in the appropriate section.

Click on the **Advanced settings **link to open the corresponding window.

#### Configuring the output
![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Option**

**Description**

**Target**

Select one of the targets created in the project.

**Spool Format**

Select one of the spool formats of the selected target.

**Enable output settings**

Activate further output settings.

**Serializer**

Select one of the serializers created in the project.

**File and metadata**

Select one of the files and metadata of the selected serializer.

**Overprint**

Enable overprint for the selected serializer.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

> Note

For more information, see: Output View.

#### Setting values to custom fields
![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Option**

**Description**

**Job Id**

Input a Job ID.

**Random**

Set a random Job ID of up to 4 digits.

**Lot Id**

Input a Lot ID.

**Random**

Set a random Lot ID of up to 4 digits.

**Field 1 .. 10 Value**

Double click to enter a custom value.s

#### Generating statistics
This panel allows to generate statistics for the run.

> Note

Currently, it is only used for compatibility with projects created with a previous project designer. It is a compatibility feature not used in new projects.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Option**

**Description**

**Enable rule statistics**

Enable the generation of statistics of the run. Not used with the current version of designer.

## Running the preview
- Select the documents you wish to preview.

- Click on the **Start **button.

- Select the XML data file to be linked to the preview.

> Note

The operation will generally take a few seconds. The processing time may vary according to the level of performance of the environment on which the product is installed and the complexity of the document.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,) 

## Viewing preview results
The preview can be either "successful" or "failed". In both cases, the status is displayed along with a green or red icon, respectively.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

In case of a failed preview, the report displays a series of diagnostic messages of the problems encountered which caused the preview to fail.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

> Tip

You can use the Copy in the notes button to export the contents of the report to the clipboard.

Troubleshooting preview failures

> Your title goes here

For a comprehensive list of the messages that may be displayed in the report at the end of the verification check, including the necessary actions to resolve any anomalies and the team responsible for solving th*e* problem, see: DC Verification Messages: Problems and Solutions.

### **Repeating the preview**
Click the **Repeat preview **button. The preview will be re-run with the same XML data file.

### Running a preview using a new XML data file
- Click the **Change file **button.

- Select the new XML data file to be linked to the preview.

### Downloading the spool produced
- Click the **Download spool **button.

- Select the local path where to save the file.

> Warning

If the preview has failed, the Download archive function may not be enabled.

### Downloading the archive produced
- Click the **Download archive **button.

- Select the local path where to save the file.

### Copying the report in the clipboard
Click the **Copy in the notes **button to copy an XML formatted report to the Clipboard.
